You are implementing the Stage 5 Audio Sync Pipeline panel (`components/stages/Stage5AudioSync.tsx`) for a video production pipeline editor. This client component manages section grouping configuration, triggers the audio sync pipeline, and displays a word timestamp viewer.

Requirements
1. Props: `onAdvance: () => void`.
2. Top section: section grouping table showing which TTS segments map to each section. Inline-editable segment ranges per section row. [Save Config] PUTs updated `audioSync.sectionGroups` to `/api/project`.
3. [Run Audio Sync] button: POSTs to `/api/pipeline/audio-sync/run`. Shows `SseLogPanel` with returned `jobId`.
4. Bottom section: Word Timestamp Viewer — table with columns: word, start (seconds to 3dp), end (seconds to 3dp), segmentId. Section filter dropdown (loads sections from project config). Search input filters by word text.
5. Virtual scrolling for large timestamp lists: use CSS `contain: strict` with fixed row heights or `react-virtual`/`@tanstack/react-virtual` if available, otherwise simple CSS approach.
6. Load timestamps: `GET /api/pipeline/audio-sync/timestamps?section={sectionId}`.
7. `'use client'` directive.

Dependencies

